  <summary date="2023-01-11T19:36:24Z" status="Introduced in House">Federal Carbon Dioxide Removal Leadership Act of 2022

This bill requires the Department of Energy to remove and permanently store, as is economically feasible, specified amounts of carbon dioxide on a specified schedule, culminating in 10 million net metric tons of carbon dioxide removal for FY2035 and each fiscal year thereafter.</summary>
